title: Hunter-gatherers would clear competing plants to allow the ones they wanted to grow to grow, and take only the part of the plant that let it live, so that it could keep growing, and aerate the soil when they took something out of it. At least some hunter-gatherers did all of these things. The only thing left that they would need to do in order to qualify as farmers is to transplant the seeds intentionally
pid: 70dc7dfd-b466-475b-a75a-8d0a2d032c52
